Network Booting
---------------

In order to boot Linux via the network, the Python web server should be setup as indicated above with the fitImage populated for booting.

--------
NFS Boot
--------

In order to boot Linux via NFS, the NFS server should be setup as indicated in `Setting Up Your Host PC: Configure NFS Server <Setting-Up-Your-Host-PC.html#configure-nfs-server>`_.

The root filesystem should then be copied to ``/romfs``.

.. code-block:: shell

   sudo tar -xf tmp/deploy/images/{{ machine }}/adsp-sc5xx-full-{{ machine }}.{{ file_extension }} -C /romfs

Next, on the target, from u-boot, run the following commands:

.. code-block:: shell

   => setenv ipaddr <IPADDR>
   => setenv serverip <SERVERIP>
   => run nfsboot
   ......
   ......
{{linux_boot_output | indent(3, True)}}

