Booting Linux Using eMMC
---------------------------
{% if sc598_sdcard %}
If booting Linux off the eMMC, make sure to build without the `ADSP_SC598_SDCARD` selected (this is the default setting), so that the eMMC is selected as the mmc device.

{% endif %}

Program the eMMC using the init script mmc instructions above.

---------------------------------
Booting from the eMMC
---------------------------------

Now, boot to U-boot and interrupt autoboot to drop to the shell and enter the following command

.. code-block:: shell

   => run mmcboot

{% endif %}

{% if has_sdcard_boot %}

Booting Linux Using SD Card
---------------------------
{% if sc598_sdcard %}
If booting Linux off the SD card, make sure to build with the `ADSP_SC598_SDCARD` selected. When the `ADSP_SC598_SDCARD` is selected, the SD card replaces the eMMC as the mmc device in Linux, and will automatically be programmed if `Y` is entered during the
mmc part of the init script.

{% endif %}

Program the SD card using the init script mmc instructions above.

Alternatively, the SD card can be programmed by the host PC before being inserted into the board.

